Summary

contract hardening day

Today was about turning the Pi-coded-agent path from a mostly documented integration into a tighter execution contract. The center of gravity was not feature breadth; it was making the coding delegation pipeline more explicit, more bounded, and more observable at the seams where work leaves Guardian and comes back through the system.

The day also carried a documentation and truth-alignment layer. The code path, the queue boundary, the worker shape, and the operational runbook all moved together so the system is easier to reason about without pretending we have live proof we do not yet have.

What I completed

Thread contract hardening

