- Added a focused live compose proof task document for the full end-to-end verification path, including enqueue, dequeue, terminal state, event lifecycle, and duplicate prevention checks.

Important outcome

The coding pipeline is no longer just a route that implies work will happen. It now has a real boundary: request in, queue, worker, result back through Guardian, with the thread lineage kept intact.

That matters because the system stopped relying on implicit behavior and started expressing the delegation contract in code, queue topology, and operator docs. It is still not live-validated end-to-end in the evidence from today, but it is structurally much closer to something that can be proven rather than assumed.

